Tue Mar 21 14:44:41 2000  Steve Totten  <totten_s@ociweb.com>

The files in this directory demonstrate a possible bug in TAO's
implementation of PortableServer::POA::servant_to_id() when the POA has
the USE_DEFAULT_SERVANT policy.

The idea is to run the server, then run the client.  The client passes a
string to the server and the server echos it back to the client.  The
client then exits.

Echo.idl

  A simple Echo interface specification.

DefaultEcho_i.{h,cpp}

  Implementation class for the Echo interface, used as a Default
  Servant.
  
EchoServer.cpp

  Server mainline which creates a child POA with the appropriate
  policies and sets an instance of DefaultEcho_i as the default servant
  on the child POA.  Then, the server generates two unique object
  references, stringifies them, and writes them to two files in the
  current directory (hardcoded):  EchoObject_1.ior and EchoObject_2.ior.

client.cpp

  A simple client to test the behavior of the EchoServer.

Makefile

  A Makefile to build the whole mess.


To run the test:

  The test assumes a build of ACE+TAO with exceptions=1.

  ./EchoServer &  # writes the files EchoObject_1.ior and EchoObject_2.ior

  ./client file://EchoObject_1.ior <optional quoted string>

